Legislative Libraries[edit]

The legislative libraries are commonly known in Australia as parliamentary libraries.[4] Amongst this group of libraries are some of the oldest libraries in Australia.[5] The Parliamentary Library in New South Wales is the oldest and was established in 1840.[5][6] The most recent parliamentary library to be established in 1989 is the ACT Legislative Assembly Library.[5][7]

Local Libraries[edit]

Local libraries are united behind common goals and ambitions, share best practice and provide universal free access to information, knowledge and ideas. They are supported by every state and territory in Australia and are often managed within Local Government areas.
